When the principal recommends students to three universities, the distribution of students can only be 1, 1, and 2. There are a total of $C_4^2 \times A_3^3 = 36$ ways;  
When recommending to two universities, the distribution of students can only be 2 and 2. There are a total of $C_3^2 \times C_4^2 = 18$ ways. Therefore, there are a total of $36 + 18 = 54$ ways.  
Hence, the correct option is $\boxed{D}$.

